How the site is built
===

This site is built using the [Quasar Framework](https://quasar-framework.org/) and deployed as a single page application

## Pages 

Pages such as this one are written in markdown and automatically added to the site. This keeps everything static and means no database is needed to fetch content.

The following script is used: 

```
const fs = require("fs")
const path = require("path")

const markdown_dir = "./markdown"

const markdown_files = fs.readdirSync(markdown_dir)
const index = []
const articles = []
let filePath

markdown_files.forEach( (file, i) => {
	filePath = path.join(__dirname, markdown_dir, file); 
	let content =	fs.readFileSync(filePath, {encoding: 'utf-8'})
	file = file.replace(/\.[^/.]+$/, "")
	// add articles to index
	index.push({
		title: file,
		id: i
	})

	// add content 
	articles.push({
		title: file,
		content: content
	})


})

fs.writeFileSync('./src/statics/index.json', JSON.stringify(index))
fs.writeFileSync('./src/statics/content.json', JSON.stringify(articles))
```
